-- Lukoil, Norilsk, Razgulay, Rosneft May Move Today: Russian Equity Preview
-- Anastasia Ustinova
-- 2010-07-30T00:38:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/lukoil-norilsk-razgulay-rosneft-may-move-today-russian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based  Micex Index  added 1.7 percent to
1,418.35 in Moscow.  
      OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Lukoil, Russia’s second-largest oil
producer, may have its long-term corporate credit rating cut one
level to junk from BBB- should the company decide to buy more
than 7.6 percent of its own shares from ConocoPhillips, Standard
& Poor’s Rating Services said. Lukoil rose 0.6 percent to
1,759.79 rubles.  
 OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper rose to a 12-week
high on speculation that the global economy will be resilient
and metal demand will improve. Russia’s largest mining company
added 1.8 percent to 5,080.13 rubles.  
 OAO Razgulay  (GRAZ RX): Wheat rose to a 13-month high,
while corn and soybean extended gains, as hot, dry weather
damaged crops from Russian to France, boosting demand for
supplies from the U.S. The Russian grain and sugar producer
added 1.2 percent 44.232 rubles.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil rose for the first time in
a week as the dollar weakened against the euro, boosting appeal
of commodities as an alternative investment. Shares rose 1.6
percent to 205.26 rubles.  
